Language used suggested that Ireland as a whole has or had a Protestant Majority. This was never the case, since partition the Republic (prior to 1949 the Irish Free State) has always had a Catholic majority of 90%+). Northern Ireland had a 65% Protestant majority in 1921. Today the Protestant to Catholic split is around 49% to 47% (apparently).
